WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.058 --> 00:00:01.599
EUNICE KIM: We
launched a new section

00:00:01.599 --> 00:00:05.070
on the Google Play Store
filled with really awesome kids

00:00:05.070 --> 00:00:06.260
and family apps.

00:00:06.260 --> 00:00:09.260
Those apps are part of our
design for families program.

00:00:09.260 --> 00:00:11.060
And for the past
12 months, we've

00:00:11.060 --> 00:00:14.140
been continuing to build on the
suite of features and services

00:00:14.140 --> 00:00:16.580
that we offer to
families who cross play,

00:00:16.580 --> 00:00:19.470
and I wanted to briefly
recap some of our most

00:00:19.470 --> 00:00:21.467
recent launches before
we get into the meat

00:00:21.467 --> 00:00:22.300
of the presentation.

00:00:25.130 --> 00:00:26.750
So first of all,
we've been working

00:00:26.750 --> 00:00:30.690
on refining our understanding
of parents as a user segment,

00:00:30.690 --> 00:00:32.610
and finding ways
both big and small

00:00:32.610 --> 00:00:35.660
to personalize their
experiences on Google Play.

00:00:35.660 --> 00:00:38.300
I'll just give you one
small example of this.

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:40.065
This is the family
category quick link

00:00:40.065 --> 00:00:41.440
that you're seeing
on the screen.

00:00:41.440 --> 00:00:43.910
This is the little
green family button,

00:00:43.910 --> 00:00:47.640
and we've made this more visible
for the parent user segment

00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:50.750
by placing it front and
center on the Play homepage.

00:00:50.750 --> 00:00:54.300
This small change resulted in
a really substantial uplift

00:00:54.300 --> 00:00:56.570
for family apps on Google Play.

00:00:56.570 --> 00:01:00.190
We've also added on to our most
popular feature for families:

00:01:00.190 --> 00:01:02.150
browsing by character.

00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:04.220
In the last 12 months
since our launch,

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:08.870
we've added another 34 beloved
characters on the Play Store

00:01:08.870 --> 00:01:11.520
globally, including one that
I think everyone in the room

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:15.210
will recognize, and this
is Angry Birds, of course.

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:17.650
And character painted
pages-- they show off

00:01:17.650 --> 00:01:22.160
a curated collection of movies,
TV shows, apps and games,

00:01:22.160 --> 00:01:25.900
books, and even music albums
associated with the character.

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:28.650
So I don't know if anyone here's
excited to see Angry Birds

00:01:28.650 --> 00:01:30.240
the Movie in a couple of days.

00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:31.510
I know that my kids are.

00:01:31.510 --> 00:01:34.090
They've been watching the
release date pretty closely.

00:01:34.090 --> 00:01:36.620
And when Angry Birds the Movie
comes out on Google Play,

00:01:36.620 --> 00:01:38.640
you'll be able to find
it all in one place here

00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:39.770
on the character page.

00:01:39.770 --> 00:01:42.270
And we're making this
page far more discoverable

00:01:42.270 --> 00:01:44.050
through search,
through featuring,

00:01:44.050 --> 00:01:48.070
et cetera, all across
the Play Store.

00:01:48.070 --> 00:01:50.040
Now beyond the store,
we've also been

00:01:50.040 --> 00:01:52.480
spending more time
thinking deeply

00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:55.450
about how to offer families
more premium services,

00:01:55.450 --> 00:01:59.080
and better support family
interactions across Android.

00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:01.650
So last December, we launched
the Google Play Music family

00:02:01.650 --> 00:02:02.540
plan.

00:02:02.540 --> 00:02:04.450
This is a subscription
that gives up

00:02:04.450 --> 00:02:07.950
to six people in your family
unlimited music for just

00:02:07.950 --> 00:02:09.815
$14.99 a month.

00:02:09.815 --> 00:02:11.440
Now, if you were
buying this separately

00:02:11.440 --> 00:02:14.240
for each family member, that
would actually cost you $60,

00:02:14.240 --> 00:02:16.340
so it's actually a
pretty great value.

00:02:16.340 --> 00:02:18.350
And we throw in YouTube
Red on top of that,

00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:22.530
so your whole family can
enjoy YouTube ads free.

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:25.300
This is obviously-- here,
you guys are app developers.

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:27.897
Why am I talking to you
about this music plan?

00:02:27.897 --> 00:02:29.480
Now when you lift
up the hood, there's

00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:31.320
something really
important going on here

00:02:31.320 --> 00:02:34.690
that's relevant for our
app developer community.

00:02:34.690 --> 00:02:37.970
When you actually get into
these premium services,

00:02:37.970 --> 00:02:39.830
you need to create
a family group,

00:02:39.830 --> 00:02:42.530
so we start understanding
who's in your family.

00:02:42.530 --> 00:02:45.250
And the eligibility for these
types of family services

00:02:45.250 --> 00:02:48.780
are anchored around a shared
family payment method.

00:02:48.780 --> 00:02:52.400
Now, this really opens up
some interesting possibilities

00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:56.190
in terms of interactions
around payments on Google.

00:02:56.190 --> 00:02:57.840
As we all know, it's
really difficult

00:02:57.840 --> 00:03:00.110
to get users to put
their credit card down,

00:03:00.110 --> 00:03:04.690
and a lot of our audience,
children and younger audiences,

00:03:04.690 --> 00:03:06.780
they don't necessarily
have access to credit,

00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:10.160
or the existing options wouldn't
have been particularly secure

00:03:10.160 --> 00:03:10.900
for them.

00:03:10.900 --> 00:03:12.540
So with the family
payment method,

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:15.590
family members can buy almost
anything on Google Play,

00:03:15.590 --> 00:03:18.260
including paid apps,
in app purchases,

00:03:18.260 --> 00:03:21.730
and other kinds of
digital content.

00:03:21.730 --> 00:03:23.650
So how does that work exactly?

00:03:23.650 --> 00:03:26.720
This is something that's live,
you could test it out yourself.

00:03:26.720 --> 00:03:29.140
Let's take a closer
look at this scenario.

00:03:29.140 --> 00:03:32.040
Imagine my teenager is playing
Transformers Rescue Bots,

00:03:32.040 --> 00:03:35.025
and he wants to buy the
two bots bundle for $5.

00:03:35.025 --> 00:03:37.230
Well he doesn't have
a credit card yet,

00:03:37.230 --> 00:03:38.680
he used up his
Play gift card that

00:03:38.680 --> 00:03:40.580
is grandmother gave
him a month ago,

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.420
and instead of
abandoning the purchase,

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.190
or worse yet, heckling
me for my credit card,

00:03:45.190 --> 00:03:47.410
where I have to add
that to his account,

00:03:47.410 --> 00:03:49.930
he can actually use the
family payment method.

00:03:49.930 --> 00:03:53.040
For in-app purchases, we
provide the family manager

00:03:53.040 --> 00:03:55.530
with a feature called
purchase approvals.

00:03:55.530 --> 00:03:58.110
This means that I have to
actually approve the purchase

00:03:58.110 --> 00:03:59.690
before it goes through.

00:03:59.690 --> 00:04:01.816
Now if it was my husband
making the purchase,

00:04:01.816 --> 00:04:03.940
well I don't really want
to bother with all of that

00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:06.290
because I do trust him,
so I have the option

00:04:06.290 --> 00:04:08.290
of turning this setting off.

00:04:08.290 --> 00:04:11.550
And note that the family payment
method is an optional feature

00:04:11.550 --> 00:04:12.190
for families.

00:04:12.190 --> 00:04:13.344
No one is forced to use it.

00:04:13.344 --> 00:04:14.760
Even when you're
part of a family,

00:04:14.760 --> 00:04:17.140
it's just one more
additional payment method

00:04:17.140 --> 00:04:19.550
that is available for
your family members.

00:04:19.550 --> 00:04:21.839
So the family group and
the family payment method

00:04:21.839 --> 00:04:25.460
are things we'll be continuing
to build on this year,

00:04:25.460 --> 00:04:28.010
and you probably saw a
little note in your inbox

00:04:28.010 --> 00:04:31.902
yesterday about family
library, which is coming.

00:04:31.902 --> 00:04:34.110
I don't have more to share
about that at this moment,

00:04:34.110 --> 00:04:36.290
but you can expect a
little bit more news

00:04:36.290 --> 00:04:39.140
on this in a few months.

00:04:39.140 --> 00:04:41.590
So with that, let's pivot to
our main topic today, which

00:04:41.590 --> 00:04:43.770
is about building
family-friendly apps

00:04:43.770 --> 00:04:46.552
and a family-friendly
business on Google Play.

00:04:46.552 --> 00:04:48.510
Now we know all of you
sitting in the audience,

00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:50.310
you're developers of
kids and family apps.

00:04:50.310 --> 00:04:51.597
Some of you are educators.

00:04:51.597 --> 00:04:53.430
Some of you are here
because you're parents,

00:04:53.430 --> 00:04:55.760
or you're just still
young at heart.

00:04:55.760 --> 00:04:58.710
You hear about all the great
Android and Google APIs,

00:04:58.710 --> 00:05:01.304
and you're wondering to
yourself can I use that service?

00:05:01.304 --> 00:05:02.970
Is there a right way
to use that service

00:05:02.970 --> 00:05:04.462
as a kids' app developer?

00:05:04.462 --> 00:05:05.920
We know it's hard
to figure out how

00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:08.870
to navigate the intersection
of Google and kids apps,

00:05:08.870 --> 00:05:11.070
so we wanted to give you
some helpful tips on how

00:05:11.070 --> 00:05:14.250
to use our services and APIs.

00:05:14.250 --> 00:05:16.920
So, first of all, let's
talk about your apps.

00:05:16.920 --> 00:05:19.920
Your app probably falls
into one of these 2 buckets.

00:05:19.920 --> 00:05:22.440
Either you're making an app
that's developed primarily

00:05:22.440 --> 00:05:24.640
for kids, or you're
making an app

00:05:24.640 --> 00:05:27.900
that's meant to be enjoyed
by both kids and adults.

00:05:27.900 --> 00:05:30.385
Now, if your app doesn't
fall into either of these two

00:05:30.385 --> 00:05:32.132
buckets, then you
probably don't need

00:05:32.132 --> 00:05:34.340
to be sitting in this session
unless you're just here

00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:36.837
for the air conditioning.

00:05:36.837 --> 00:05:37.420
Let's move on.

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:42.200
Just keep it in mind which
type of app you have.

00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:45.985
Now, if you have an app that's
designed for kids and families,

00:05:45.985 --> 00:05:47.360
here's the easiest
tip of the day

00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:49.470
that we'll give you, which
is joining the Design

00:05:49.470 --> 00:05:50.780
for Families program.

00:05:50.780 --> 00:05:51.447
Why?

00:05:51.447 --> 00:05:53.280
Well it's better for
your apps and it's also

00:05:53.280 --> 00:05:54.850
better for our users.

00:05:54.850 --> 00:05:56.880
So most of you already
know about the benefits

00:05:56.880 --> 00:05:59.840
of this program, but I'll
just quickly recap it.

00:05:59.840 --> 00:06:02.210
You have an opportunity to
be featured in the family

00:06:02.210 --> 00:06:03.940
category on Google Play.

00:06:03.940 --> 00:06:06.230
You get to rank and top
chart your family apps,

00:06:06.230 --> 00:06:09.390
in addition to regular
top charts in the games

00:06:09.390 --> 00:06:11.030
or the apps section.

00:06:11.030 --> 00:06:13.060
You can be discovered in
search queries relating

00:06:13.060 --> 00:06:14.160
to kids content.

00:06:14.160 --> 00:06:15.457
We boost you up.

00:06:15.457 --> 00:06:17.790
And you get recognized in the
store with the family star

00:06:17.790 --> 00:06:20.160
badge, which is something
that our users look

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:23.350
for to understand whether or
not your app is family friendly.

00:06:23.350 --> 00:06:26.600
We also collect more
information about the target age

00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:29.460
of your app, the specific
category that you're targeting.

00:06:29.460 --> 00:06:32.690
This actually helps us
do more on the back end

00:06:32.690 --> 00:06:35.140
to make sure that we're
actually pushing the right apps

00:06:35.140 --> 00:06:37.230
to the right types of users.

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:39.970
Now, whether you're part of
the Design for Families program

00:06:39.970 --> 00:06:42.750
or not, the way
that kids interact

00:06:42.750 --> 00:06:45.126
with Google and
Android APIs does

00:06:45.126 --> 00:06:46.500
require some
additional tweaking,

00:06:46.500 --> 00:06:49.020
so we're going to dive
into that a bit right now.

00:06:51.920 --> 00:06:54.270
OK, so let's talk about ads.

00:06:54.270 --> 00:06:56.520
This is probably the
area that most of you

00:06:56.520 --> 00:06:58.060
want to know the most about.

00:06:58.060 --> 00:07:01.159
Now, if your app is targeting
kids as part of its audience,

00:07:01.159 --> 00:07:03.450
you probably know there are
a lot of legal requirements

00:07:03.450 --> 00:07:06.890
for respecting child privacy in
different parts of the world.

00:07:06.890 --> 00:07:09.790
And if you're using Admob
as one of your ad networks,

00:07:09.790 --> 00:07:14.020
then Admob actually offers an
option for dealing with this.

00:07:14.020 --> 00:07:15.880
And this is a
pretty simple thing.

00:07:15.880 --> 00:07:18.700
When you basically go to
request an ad from Admob,

00:07:18.700 --> 00:07:21.990
you just tag the ad request
in your app with a tag

00:07:21.990 --> 00:07:25.920
that we call TFCD, and
that stands for Tag

00:07:25.920 --> 00:07:27.850
For Child Directed Treatment.

00:07:27.850 --> 00:07:30.830
This basically turns off
interest-based advertising

00:07:30.830 --> 00:07:34.054
and re-marketing
in the ad request.

00:07:34.054 --> 00:07:35.470
There's another
common requirement

00:07:35.470 --> 00:07:37.320
in many parts of
the world, and this

00:07:37.320 --> 00:07:40.410
is that the ad content you need
to display inside a kids' app

00:07:40.410 --> 00:07:42.900
needs to be age appropriate.

00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:45.530
When you need a
kid-friendly ad, Admob

00:07:45.530 --> 00:07:47.880
does offer an option
for this as well.

00:07:47.880 --> 00:07:52.310
This is what we call KFA, which
stands for Kid Friendly Ad.

00:07:52.310 --> 00:07:55.790
So again, all you simply
do is tag your ad request

00:07:55.790 --> 00:07:58.280
with this particular
tag and we'll actually

00:07:58.280 --> 00:08:03.042
deliver kid friendly content in
the advertisement to your app.

00:08:03.042 --> 00:08:04.750
Now if you're
participating in the Design

00:08:04.750 --> 00:08:07.730
for Families program, and
your primarily targeting kids,

00:08:07.730 --> 00:08:09.830
Google will automatically
tag your ad requests,

00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:12.750
so you don't have to do
that work on your end.

00:08:12.750 --> 00:08:14.660
But otherwise, you'll
need to make sure

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:20.370
that you're actually adding this
into your ad request directly.

00:08:20.370 --> 00:08:22.810
Now, you may have noticed
that we also recently started

00:08:22.810 --> 00:08:26.620
displaying this little label
on the details pages for apps.

00:08:26.620 --> 00:08:29.960
And this is a little
label that tells

00:08:29.960 --> 00:08:32.386
users hey, my app
actually contains ads,

00:08:32.386 --> 00:08:34.344
because this is one of
our top feature requests

00:08:34.344 --> 00:08:38.409
from parents on the Play Store.

00:08:38.409 --> 00:08:40.799
Since this past January,
in Developer Console

00:08:40.799 --> 00:08:43.559
you'll notice that there's a
section where you can actually

00:08:43.559 --> 00:08:46.800
tell us yes, my app does
in fact contain ads,

00:08:46.800 --> 00:08:50.150
and this will actually help
speed up your review process.

00:08:50.150 --> 00:08:51.890
We know that everyone
is always eager

00:08:51.890 --> 00:08:54.900
to get their apps on to the
store as soon as possible,

00:08:54.900 --> 00:08:56.300
so make sure that
you're actually

00:08:56.300 --> 00:08:59.125
checking this box if your app in
fact does contain advertising.

00:09:02.390 --> 00:09:05.370
Now let's talk about
Google Play Games services.

00:09:05.370 --> 00:09:07.920
Has anyone here tried out
the auto login feature

00:09:07.920 --> 00:09:10.581
that we recently
launched in February?

00:09:10.581 --> 00:09:11.080
No?

00:09:11.080 --> 00:09:11.730
Maybe not.

00:09:11.730 --> 00:09:12.230
OK.

00:09:12.230 --> 00:09:14.120
Well you should check it out.

00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:16.390
Play Games, as you
know, offers a variety

00:09:16.390 --> 00:09:19.250
of features like leader
boards, achievements,

00:09:19.250 --> 00:09:23.000
multi-player games, and even
video recording inside the app.

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:24.650
Now unfortunately,
we can't necessarily

00:09:24.650 --> 00:09:28.420
offer these features to
children under the age of 13,

00:09:28.420 --> 00:09:32.700
since Google accounts are made
for children ages 13 and up,

00:09:32.700 --> 00:09:34.240
or users aged 13 and up

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:35.650
So here's really
the key takeaway

00:09:35.650 --> 00:09:37.530
for developers of kids' apps.

00:09:37.530 --> 00:09:40.470
First, if your app is really
primarily targeting just

00:09:40.470 --> 00:09:43.180
children, you shouldn't
integrate the game service.

00:09:43.180 --> 00:09:44.690
Really, really basic.

00:09:44.690 --> 00:09:47.930
Now, if your app is targeting
both kids and adults,

00:09:47.930 --> 00:09:50.280
you can integrate the
Play Games service,

00:09:50.280 --> 00:09:52.257
you just need to make
sure that it's optional.

00:09:52.257 --> 00:09:54.090
There's two different
implementation options

00:09:54.090 --> 00:09:56.392
when you read through
this in our documentation.

00:09:56.392 --> 00:09:57.850
You just need to
make sure that you

00:09:57.850 --> 00:10:00.450
choose the optional
implementation rather

00:10:00.450 --> 00:10:01.710
than the auto login version.

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:08.090
Another really great
feature for kids is speech,

00:10:08.090 --> 00:10:10.110
and using voice-based
applications

00:10:10.110 --> 00:10:14.150
makes a lot of sense for kids'
apps because a lot of our users

00:10:14.150 --> 00:10:17.640
they don't [INAUDIBLE]
yet, they don't necessarily

00:10:17.640 --> 00:10:21.050
know how to spell well and
they're probably not typing

00:10:21.050 --> 00:10:22.820
that proficiently on a device.

00:10:22.820 --> 00:10:25.400
So, as you know, Android
offers a world class speech

00:10:25.400 --> 00:10:28.480
API which can be used to power
things like voice search,

00:10:28.480 --> 00:10:31.010
like we have here in
our YouTube kid's app.

00:10:31.010 --> 00:10:33.890
Now, audio recording is
a sensitive privacy area

00:10:33.890 --> 00:10:35.730
for kids' apps, and
we know some of you

00:10:35.730 --> 00:10:38.150
may be wary about adding
these types of features

00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:40.670
because you didn't know
how to go about it.

00:10:40.670 --> 00:10:43.830
Well, I'm happy to tell you that
the Android speech API actually

00:10:43.830 --> 00:10:47.240
offers a way for
you to tell us when

00:10:47.240 --> 00:10:50.710
you want us to treat the voice
search requests in your app

00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:52.310
with more sensitivity.

00:10:52.310 --> 00:10:54.960
Similar to the ad situation,
all you need to do

00:10:54.960 --> 00:10:57.200
is send a special tag
with your request,

00:10:57.200 --> 00:10:59.450
and if you're part of the
Design for Families program,

00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:01.760
again, we take care
of this for you

00:11:01.760 --> 00:11:04.440
and we're actually tagging
all of your voice requests

00:11:04.440 --> 00:11:05.880
on your behalf on the back end.

00:11:08.550 --> 00:11:10.672
Finally, the most important
tip of the day: you

00:11:10.672 --> 00:11:12.380
don't have to keep
this all in your head.

00:11:12.380 --> 00:11:14.820
You don't have to furiously
scribble down notes.

00:11:14.820 --> 00:11:17.920
We'll be including all of
this material in a new section

00:11:17.920 --> 00:11:20.450
in our Developer
Policy Center that's

00:11:20.450 --> 00:11:23.970
called Kids and Families This is
coming in June, and all of this

00:11:23.970 --> 00:11:26.350
will be covered in detail
with obviously a lot more

00:11:26.350 --> 00:11:30.520
technical instruction on how to
do the ad tagging, et cetera.

