00:14:01.130 --> 00:14:02.450
Closed beta?

00:14:02.450 --> 00:14:03.810
OK, cool.

00:14:03.810 --> 00:14:06.290
So basically for those
who may not be familiar,

00:14:06.290 --> 00:14:09.910
alpha and beta testing is
a way for you to check out

00:14:09.910 --> 00:14:11.790
new app features you
may be launching,

00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:17.790
or even your new app, to a
smaller group of select users

00:14:17.790 --> 00:14:20.025
before you launch it out
to the world in general.

00:14:20.025 --> 00:14:21.400
And this allows
them to check it,

00:14:21.400 --> 00:14:24.490
to give you feedback, for you
to catch bugs and fix them

00:14:24.490 --> 00:14:27.330
before it's released into
kind of the big wide world

00:14:27.330 --> 00:14:30.630
and any bugs affect your rating.

00:14:30.630 --> 00:14:35.160
So with an open beta, it can be
open to pretty much anyone who

00:14:35.160 --> 00:14:37.970
wants it, though you can
cap the amount of people.

00:14:37.970 --> 00:14:40.930
You don't have to worry about
creating that beta community.

00:14:40.930 --> 00:14:44.620
But if you only want to use
it for a specific audience,

00:14:44.620 --> 00:14:47.725
then you have the option of
creating a closed community

00:14:47.725 --> 00:14:53.150
with the list of emails to be
beta testers off your content.

00:14:53.150 --> 00:15:00.700
And in fact, at I/O, we
launched the ability for you to,

00:15:00.700 --> 00:15:03.330
if you have an
open beta, for user

00:15:03.330 --> 00:15:06.934
to sign into that from
the store listing itself.

00:15:06.934 --> 00:15:08.350
So if I go into
the store listing,

00:15:08.350 --> 00:15:14.140
and an app has an open beta,
I can select to beta the app.

00:15:16.920 --> 00:15:20.230
For a select group
of apps, we'll

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:22.270
be featuring them in
a collection, called

00:15:22.270 --> 00:15:24.260
an early access
collection, to expose

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:27.290
our users to really promising
open betas that are not

00:15:27.290 --> 00:15:30.640
in production yet.

