00:17:15.710 --> 00:17:18.819
actually increase
the installs by 10%.

00:17:18.819 --> 00:17:21.900
And so they ended up
converting to that icon.

00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:24.750
Rovio has tried a bunch
of different experiments,

00:17:24.750 --> 00:17:27.839
and in fact now, all of their
launches are soft launches.

00:17:27.839 --> 00:17:30.680
They get the A/B testing
to get their listing right,

00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:34.270
and then they launch their
app to the general public.

00:17:34.270 --> 00:17:37.420
We also recently, I think
it was as soon as last week,

00:17:37.420 --> 00:17:40.660
announced that you can actually
run up to five store listing

00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:41.740
experiments at a time.

00:17:45.010 --> 00:17:47.260
Reviews and ratings
are really important.

00:17:47.260 --> 00:17:50.950
How many people have
responded to user reviews?

00:17:50.950 --> 00:17:52.240
OK, good.

00:17:52.240 --> 00:17:54.710
So reviews and ratings
matter in the family space

00:17:54.710 --> 00:17:56.170
more than other categories.

00:17:56.170 --> 00:17:59.730
Reason being, and I see
this in myself as a parent,

00:17:59.730 --> 00:18:02.340
parents look to other
parents for ideas,

00:18:02.340 --> 00:18:06.600
inspiration, things on
what to get their kids,

00:18:06.600 --> 00:18:09.770
stuff that will help their kids.

00:18:09.770 --> 00:18:12.920
One of the main things they
go to is ratings and reviews.

00:18:12.920 --> 00:18:14.970
But these are two
way streets, right?

00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:19.130
So you want to help build up
that community so people will

00:18:19.130 --> 00:18:20.880
engage with your app,
leave reviews, tell

00:18:20.880 --> 00:18:22.350
their friends about it.

00:18:22.350 --> 00:18:24.600
And we also recently had
announced the ability for you

00:18:24.600 --> 00:18:26.530
to respond to reviews,
which I'm glad

00:18:26.530 --> 00:18:28.900
quite a few people are
availing themselves of.

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:31.330
One of the things
we saw that when,

00:18:31.330 --> 00:18:33.720
especially if you
have low reviews,

00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:38.620
and you respond
to those reviews,

00:18:38.620 --> 00:18:40.970
quite a few users end up
then changing their rating.

00:18:40.970 --> 00:18:42.580
And they end up
raising the rating

00:18:42.580 --> 00:18:44.970
by an average of
about 0.7 stars,

00:18:44.970 --> 00:18:48.050
which is enough to get you over
maybe into the next star rating

00:18:48.050 --> 00:18:49.470
category.

00:18:49.470 --> 00:18:53.070
And star rating really
matters, because people equate

00:18:53.070 --> 00:18:54.950
star rating with quality.

00:18:54.950 --> 00:18:58.440
We've seen a very strong
correlation between quality

00:18:58.440 --> 00:19:00.750
and revenue, so getting
that rating important

00:19:00.750 --> 00:19:04.030
and doing whatever it
takes is really important.

00:19:04.030 --> 00:19:06.440
Because we recognize that,
we've done a lot of stuff

00:19:06.440 --> 00:19:08.010
on that in the
developer console.

00:19:08.010 --> 00:19:11.200
So there's the ability to
look at ratings and reviews

00:19:11.200 --> 00:19:14.320
by time segment, by country.

00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:16.890
In fact, one of my favorites
is review highlights,

00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:19.590
so you can see what are the
top themes that people are

00:19:19.590 --> 00:19:22.574
talking about your app or game.

00:19:22.574 --> 00:19:23.990
It may be very
different from what

00:19:23.990 --> 00:19:26.050
you thought your app
or game was about,

00:19:26.050 --> 00:19:28.000
and people are responding
to something else.

00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:31.020
And that helps you change your
marketing campaign, or think

00:19:31.020 --> 00:19:35.190
about an audience you
may have not considered.

00:19:35.190 --> 00:19:40.920
We also recently released
review benchmarks,

00:19:40.920 --> 00:19:45.500
which lets you compare your
app to other similar apps

00:19:45.500 --> 00:19:48.230
in your category
across common topics,

00:19:48.230 --> 00:19:51.560
like speed or
stability, et cetera,

00:19:51.560 --> 00:19:55.110
so you can see how your
app compares to those-- how

00:19:55.110 --> 00:19:58.060
do your ratings compare
to other similar apps

00:19:58.060 --> 00:20:01.000
across those dimensions,
and make any fixes.

00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:03.140
We also allow you
the ability to be

00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:07.620
able to measure your rating on
topics specific to your app,

00:20:07.620 --> 00:20:12.120
and see where it is that
you are falling behind

00:20:12.120 --> 00:20:14.130
so you can make improvements.

00:20:14.130 --> 00:20:16.580
We recognize how important
ratings and reviews are,

00:20:16.580 --> 00:20:18.390
so there will be a
lot of effort made

00:20:18.390 --> 00:20:23.140
to help you understand
them and make them go up.

